---
layout: base.njk
---
{% set waUrl = site | waUrl %}

{% include "nav.njk" %}
{% include "hero.njk" %}

{# ========== TRUST BAR ========== #}
{% if site.showTrustBar %}
<section class="bg-navy-light border-y border-white/5 py-6">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
      <div class="reveal stagger-1">
        <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-emerald">{{ site.stats.properties }}</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-xs sm:text-sm mt-1">Properties Metered</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal stagger-2">
        <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-emerald">{{ site.stats.units }}</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-xs sm:text-sm mt-1">Units Installed</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal stagger-3">
        <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white">{{ site.stats.monthlyFees }}</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-xs sm:text-sm mt-1">Monthly Fees</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal stagger-4">
        <p class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-white">{{ site.stats.installTime }}</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-xs sm:text-sm mt-1">Typical Install</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

{# ========== THE ACTUAL PROBLEM ========== #}
<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-surface-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-14">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-[2.75rem] text-navy leading-tight mb-5" style="text-wrap: balance;">
        Here's what I keep hearing from landlords
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="reveal">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">"I have no idea who's using what."</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          You've got one hydro bill. Four units. One of them is running two space heaters all winter. You're paying for all of it and you can't prove anything.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">"I tried splitting it evenly and it blew up."</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Someone's working from home with three monitors. Someone else is gone 12 hours a day. Even splits are never even. Everyone ends up resentful.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">"Hydro keeps going up but I can't raise rent fast enough."</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Ontario caps rent increases. Hydro doesn't care about Ontario caps. Every year the gap between what you charge and what you actually pay gets wider.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal mt-12 bg-surface rounded-2xl p-7 border border-slate-100">
      <p class="text-navy leading-relaxed">
        This isn't a hypothetical. A landlord on the Mountain had a fourplex. His hydro was $680/month. Two tenants had electric space heaters going nonstop. He had no way to know until we put meters on. Turned out one unit was using almost half the building's electricity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== IS THIS EVEN LEGAL? ========== #}
<section class="py-16 sm:py-20 bg-surface">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-emerald/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
        <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-emerald" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 21v-8.25M15.75 21v-8.25M8.25 21v-8.25M3 9l9-6 9 6m-1.5 12V10.332A48.36 48.36 0 0012 9.75c-2.551 0-5.056.2-7.5.582V21M3 21h18M12 6.75h.008v.008H12V6.75z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-navy leading-tight mb-3" style="text-wrap: balance;">
        "Am I actually allowed to charge tenants for hydro?"
      </h2>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Yeah. Ontario Regulation 394/10 under the Electricity Act says you can install sub-meters and bill tenants for their own usage. Most landlords never look into it because they assume it's complicated or not allowed. It's neither.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal stagger-1 mb-6">
      <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-5">Here's what you need:</p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="reveal stagger-1 bg-surface-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
        <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-2">Written notice to existing tenants</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">I give you the template, ready to go. You don't have to write anything.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal stagger-2 bg-surface-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
        <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-2">A rent reduction for tenants who had hydro included</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">The regulation requires it. It's basically: you lower rent by roughly what hydro was costing per unit, and then they pay their own. You come out ahead because the heavy users were costing you way more than the average.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="reveal stagger-3 bg-surface-white rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-100">
        <p class="text-navy font-semibold mb-2">For new tenants</p>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">You just write the lease without included electricity. Done.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="reveal mt-8 text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
      I walk you through the whole thing. It takes about 10 minutes to explain.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== HOW IT WORKS ========== #}
<section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 bg-navy grain overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-1/3 h-full bg-gradient-to-l from-emerald/[0.03] to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>
  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-14">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-[2.75rem] text-white leading-tight mb-5" style="text-wrap: balance;">
        This is the whole process. There's not much to it.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald text-navy font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 shadow-lg shadow-emerald/20">1</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg mb-3">I come look at your panel.</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Takes 15 minutes. I check if your building's wiring lets me isolate each unit's circuit. Most buildings do. If yours doesn't, I'll tell you on the spot and you don't owe me anything.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald text-navy font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 shadow-lg shadow-emerald/20">2</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg mb-3">I clip the meters on.</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              The meter is a small clamp that goes around the wire — like a clothespin around a cable. I don't cut anything. I don't touch the conductor. Your tenants won't know I was there. Takes about an hour for a typical fourplex.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-emerald text-navy font-bold text-lg flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 shadow-lg shadow-emerald/20">3</div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-white text-lg mb-3">You open the dashboard.</h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Same day. Each unit shows up on your phone. Hourly, daily, monthly usage. You'll finally know exactly what's happening in your building.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal mt-14">
      <div class="bg-emerald/10 rounded-xl py-5 px-6">
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          That's it. No electrician. No permits. No power shutoff. If you ever want to take the meters off, I unclip them and your panel looks exactly like it did before.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== WHAT IT ACTUALLY LOOKS LIKE ========== #}
<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-surface">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-14">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-navy leading-tight mb-5" style="text-wrap: balance;">
        What It Actually Looks Like
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      {# Before card #}
      <div class="reveal stagger-1 relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden aspect-[4/3] bg-navy-light border border-white/10">
        <img src="{{ site.images.installation }}" alt="Standard electrical panel before sub-meter installation" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-80">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-navy/70 to-transparent"></div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-navy/80 backdrop-blur-sm text-text-muted text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-2">Before</span>
          <p class="text-white font-semibold">Your panel. One meter. You pay everything.</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">No idea who uses what.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {# After card #}
      <div class="reveal stagger-2 relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden aspect-[4/3] bg-navy-light border border-emerald/20">
        <img src="{{ site.images.monitoring }}" alt="Electrical panel with clip-on current transformers installed" width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-80">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-navy/70 to-transparent"></div>
        <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 p-6">
          <span class="inline-block bg-emerald/90 text-navy text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider px-3 py-1 rounded-full mb-2">After</span>
          <p class="text-white font-semibold">Same panel. Small clamps added.</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">Each unit measured separately. Remove them anytime — zero trace.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== COST ========== #}
<section class="py-20 sm:py-24 bg-surface-white">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-navy leading-tight mb-5">
        What does it cost?
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal space-y-6">
      <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Typical range is <span class="text-navy font-semibold">{{ site.pricing.perUnit }} per unit</span> depending on your panel. A fourplex usually runs {{ site.pricing.fourplexTotal }} total.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Most landlords make that back in {{ site.pricing.roiMonths }} months.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
        I give you the exact number during the visit — before you decide anything. No surprise invoices, no add-ons.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== WHO I AM ========== #}
<section class="py-20 sm:py-24 bg-surface">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-navy leading-tight">
        {{ site.founder.name }}
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal stagger-1 bg-surface-white rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-10 border border-slate-100">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start gap-6">
        {# Placeholder avatar — replace with real photo #}
        <div class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full bg-navy flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
          <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-emerald" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M15.75 6a3.75 3.75 0 11-7.5 0 3.75 3.75 0 017.5 0zM4.501 20.118a7.5 7.5 0 0114.998 0A17.933 17.933 0 0112 21.75c-2.676 0-5.216-.584-7.499-1.632z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">I live in {{ site.founder.neighbourhood }}.</p>
          <p class="text-navy leading-relaxed">
            {{ site.founder.bio }}
          </p>
          <p class="text-navy leading-relaxed">
            {{ site.founder.bio2 }}
          </p>
          <p class="text-navy leading-relaxed">
            {{ site.founder.bio3 }}
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== FAQ ========== #}
<section class="py-20 sm:py-28 bg-surface-white">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5">
    <div class="mb-14">
      <div class="accent-line mb-6 reveal"></div>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-navy leading-tight">
        Common Questions
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      {% for item in site.faq %}
      <div class="reveal stagger-{{ loop.index if loop.index <= 4 else 4 }} faq-item bg-surface rounded-xl border border-slate-100 overflow-hidden">
        <button class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-6 text-left" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-semibold text-navy pr-4">{{ item.question }}</span>
          <span class="faq-icon text-emerald text-2xl font-light shrink-0">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer px-6">
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed pb-6">
            {{ item.answer | safe }}
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ========== FINAL CTA ========== #}
<section class="relative py-20 sm:py-28 bg-navy grain overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0">
    <img src="{{ site.images.cta }}" alt="Hamilton city skyline at dusk" width="1920" height="1080" loading="lazy" class="w-full h-full object-cover opacity-15">
  </div>
  <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-96 h-96 bg-emerald/10 rounded-full blur-[120px] pointer-events-none"></div>

  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 text-center">
    <div class="accent-line mx-auto mb-6 reveal"></div>
    <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl text-white leading-tight mb-5" style="text-wrap: balance;">
      Want to know if it works for your building?
    </h2>
    <p class="reveal stagger-1 text-text-muted text-lg mb-4 max-w-xl mx-auto">
      Message me on WhatsApp. Tell me how many units you have and roughly where the property is. I'll set up a time to come look at your panel.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal stagger-1 text-text-muted text-sm mb-10">
      No contracts &middot; No monthly fees &middot; One-time install
    </p>
    <div class="reveal stagger-2 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
      <a href="{{ waUrl }}"
         class="cta-glow inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 bg-emerald hover:bg-emerald-dark text-navy font-bold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-xl">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M17.472 14.382c-.297-.149-1.758-.867-2.03-.967-.273-.099-.471-.148-.67.15-.197.297-.767.966-.94 1.164-.173.199-.347.223-.644.075-.297-.15-1.255-.463-2.39-1.475-.883-.788-1.48-1.761-1.653-2.059-.173-.297-.018-.458.13-.606.134-.133.298-.347.446-.52.149-.174.198-.298.298-.497.099-.198.05-.371-.025-.52-.075-.149-.669-1.612-.916-2.207-.242-.579-.487-.5-.669-.51-.173-.008-.371-.01-.57-.01-.198 0-.52.074-.792.372-.272.297-1.04 1.016-1.04 2.479 0 1.462 1.065 2.875 1.213 3.074.149.198 2.096 3.2 5.077 4.487.709.306 1.262.489 1.694.625.712.227 1.36.195 1.871.118.571-.085 1.758-.719 2.006-1.413.248-.694.248-1.289.173-1.413-.074-.124-.272-.198-.57-.347z"/><path d="M12 0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12c0 2.625.846 5.059 2.284 7.034L.789 23.492a.5.5 0 00.611.611l4.458-1.495A11.952 11.952 0 0012 24c6.627 0 12-5.373 12-12S18.627 0 12 0zm0 22c-2.387 0-4.607-.798-6.382-2.147l-.446-.344-2.635.883.883-2.635-.344-.446A9.935 9.935 0 012 12C2 6.486 6.486 2 12 2s10 4.486 10 10-4.486 10-10 10z"/></svg>
        Message on WhatsApp
      </a>
      <a href="tel:{{ site.phoneLink }}"
         class="inline-flex items-center gap-2.5 bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/15 text-white font-semibold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-xl border border-white/10 transition-colors duration-200">
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 6.75c0 8.284 6.716 15 15 15h2.25a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-1.372c0-.516-.351-.966-.852-1.091l-4.423-1.106c-.44-.11-.902.055-1.173.417l-.97 1.293c-.282.376-.769.542-1.21.38a12.035 12.035 0 01-7.143-7.143c-.162-.441.004-.928.38-1.21l1.293-.97c.363-.271.527-.734.417-1.173L6.963 3.102a1.125 1.125 0 00-1.091-.852H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 002.25 4.5v2.25z"/></svg>
        Call {{ site.phoneDisplay }}
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{% include "footer.njk" %}
